course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped into ½cm pieces). Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1} and chop into 1cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Put a splash of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until soft, stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes}. Add the red pepper and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook for another ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and half the parsley. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1} and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low. Let the sauce simmer gently for ~{10%minutes}, stirring from time to time.

Meanwhile, put a good glug of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @gnocchi{300%g}. Cook until golden and crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir to turn the gnocchi occasionally so they cook evenly.

While the sauce and gnocchi are cooking, make the pesto. Roughly chop the @hazelnuts{25}(roughly chopped). Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped).

> TIP: Use scissors for this if you want!

Pop the hazelnuts, chives and half the remaining parsley into a #mixing bowl{} and add the olive oil (see ingredients for amount). Season with a pinch of salt and pepper and stir everything together well.

Once the gnocchi is golden, remove the pan from the heat. Remove the sauce from the heat as well and stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}. When the crème fraîche is mixed in, add the @baby spinach{125%g} and stir until it wilts. Taste, and add more salt and black pepper if necessary. Add the gnocchi to the sauce and mix well.

Serve the creamy tomato gnocchi in #bowls{}. Sprinkle the remaining parsley over the top, along with the hazelnut and chive pesto. Enjoy!